  "description": [
    "NVVVsi Ar0y The figures worry me he says BUSHY IS PUZZLED Bushy Barnes down at the newsstand is sufferin from a bad case of statistics Lemme check a few figures on your addin ma chine Wally Bushy asks me last night When he gets through he looks puzzled I been sort of think in I would go in the insurance business he says What worries me is the figures I been puttin down all the amounts they say we lose in various ways How do you mean Jake my partner asks This way says Bushy The paper says acci dents cost eight billion dollars a year Another place I read that fires cost six billion Here are some more floods storms rats hogcholera an miscellaneous disasters nicks us eighteen billion We lose two bil lion on strikes tax dodgers pickpockets swindlers an the underworld gets us for eleven billion Jeepers Jake whistles We are sure took The steel an iron guys claims we rust away a billion Bushy resumes The lumber guys report termites an dry rot chews up another one The oil boys get their petroleum mixed with sand an their gas mixed with air an two billion escapes"
  ],
